{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"78bbf2fd-9a55-4f35-bd88-3f0befd7c06d","content":"The directory is empty — there's no existing project yet. No problem, I can explain exactly what you need to configure. Here's the concise answer:\n\n## Publishing a C# MCP Server as a `dotnet tool`\n\nAdd these properties to your `.csproj` file:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n\n  <!-- dotnet tool packaging -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata (required for nuget.org) -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server over stdio.</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n\n<!-- Include a README in the package -->\n<ItemGroup>\n  <None Include=\"README.md\" Pack=\"true\" PackagePath=\"/\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\n### Key properties explained\n\n| Property | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `PackAsTool` | Tells `dotnet pack` to produce a tool package |\n| `ToolCommandName` | The CLI command users will invoke (e.g. `my-mcp-server`) |\n| `PackageId` | The NuGet package name users install with `dotnet tool install` |\n\n### Build, pack & publish\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server            # runs over stdio\n```\n\nThat's the minimum required configuration. `PackAsTool` + `ToolCommandName` are the critical pieces — everything else is standard NuGet metadata.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1cb74704-c1f8-4ddd-abe5-c4b128696600","outputTokens":569},"id":"74ce254c-2bf2-4591-a2a5-e470f68f18c7","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:46:14.518Z","parentId":"dbe24f75-499c-460f-8ce8-22fc02de2e68"}
